data.name: Metagrobolize
data.description:
" What is the most contagious parasite? A virus? A Bacteria? No...! It is an unsolved maths puzzle. Nothing can ever possibly cripple your brain like a puzzle can. It isolates you from the rest of the world. It pulls in anyone who is exposed. " 

Welcome to the portal of enlightenment and enjoyment. Metagrobolize is an online math event conducted by the Computer Society of MIT as a part of Carte Blanche-2014. 

The questions demand good logical reasoning ability and basic knowledge of mathematics. (Google shall help you with the latter) 

Ready for the challenge ? Metagrobolize yourselves at Carte Blanche-14

Metagrobolize (verb.)
     to baffle and disturb or flabbergast, to puzzle or mystify or perplex or mix up.

data.name: OPC Shaastra 2014
data.description:
Greetings from the Online Programming Contest team of Shaastra - 2014, IIT Madras. This year we are hosting the event on codechef(http://www.codechef.com/SHSTRA14). There is an exciting array of prizes to be won. There are prizes for Indian college students, non-Indian college students, IITM college students, Indian school students and many more! 

We have interesting formats of questions that is sure to have each and everyone enthralled. For an elaborate list of rules please refer to the codechef link given above in this mail. The contest would be held on January 4th 2014. This contest is the right practice whether you are preparing for INOI - 2014 , ACM-ICPC World finals - 2014, or just want to have some fun. To be eligible for prizes please register on http://www.shaastra.org/2014/main/#open_programming_contest . Hope to see you all participate and win lots of prizes.

data.name: CodinGame Challenge July 27
data.description:
Ready for the next CodinGame online programming contest?

When?
Saturday, July 27th 2013 starting at 4 pm (UTC).
It's online, it's worldwide, so appropriate local times can be checked here: http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=CodinGame+July&iso=20130727T18&p1=1263

Why?
An opportunity for all developers who love to code to:
- Challenge the best coders and find out how they stack up against them
- Apply to developer-friendly Tech companies they like 
- Win cash prizes & goodies

Who?
Developers from all over the world are welcome whatever their profile or experience.
They can compete from home, for jobs or just for fun.

How?
The average duration of the challenge is 2 hours 30 minutes.
The aim is to solve puzzles using one's favorite programming language (between C#, C++, C, PHP, Java, Javascript, Ruby, Python, Objective C, Go and Haskell)
Training page: http://www.codingame.com/cg/#!training

Ready to compete? Sign up here: http://www.codingame.com/cg/#!challenge:10

Of course it's free, and it's anonymous.
